Says [Wikipedia about Art Director](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Art_director):

> It is the charge of a sole art director to supervise and unify the vision. In particular, the art director is in charge of the overall visual appearance and how it communicates visually, stimulates moods, contrasts features, and psychologically appeals to a target audience. The art director makes decisions about visual elements used, what artistic style to use, and when to use motion.

I'll break this passage down, examine key words, and give examples of things I did in each situation in the quest for finding the direction for a game I'm making.

# The game

Without giving too much away at this stage, ==the game was inspired by the daily commute==. The setting is a train. And perhaps a bus, if time permits. Since no-one really writes songs about their commute, it won't convey too much sunshine and happiness.

A quick initial idea was to use hand-drawn black-and-white characters overlayed on a photograph of the interior of a train.

# Supervise

I'm a team of one due to my shoestring budget. Also, I'm challenging myself to do it all, so no easy way out with freelancers. That doesn't mean that I didn't script up my own freelancer.

## The brief

Find a few ["re-use with modification"](https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/) photos, apply a moody palette, then superimpose a prototype character onto them.

### Step 1

Go to Google Images, search for "train interior", select Large images, and "re-use with modification", then paste this bit of Vanilla Javascript into devtools:

<pre>
// thanks http://stackoverflow.com/a/28890083/51280
function download(from, to) {
  var a = document.createElement('a');
  a.href = from;
  a.download = to; // necessary?
  document.body.appendChild(a);
  a.click();
  document.body.removeChild(a);
}

function scroll() {
  window.scrollTo(0,document.body.scrollHeight);
}

function downloadAll() {
  var children = $('#rg_s').children;
  for (var i=0; i < children.length; i++) {
    var child = $('a', children[i]);
    var href = $('a', $('#rg_s').children[i]);
    if (href) {
      var imgurl = getQueryVariable(href.search, 'imgurl');
      if (imgurl) {
        download(imgurl, "output-" + i + imgurl.substring(imgurl.lastIndexOf('.')));
      }
    }
  }
}

// thanks http://stackoverflow.com/a/2091331/51280
function getQueryVariable(search, variable) {
    var query = search.substring(1);
    var vars = query.split('&');
    for (var i = 0; i < vars.length; i++) {
        var pair = vars[i].split('=');
        if (decodeURIComponent(pair[0]) == variable) {
            return decodeURIComponent(pair[1]);
        }
    }
    console.log('Query variable %s not found', variable);
}

// scroll()
// scroll()
// scroll()
downloadAll();

</pre>

